name: Dianne Primavera
tweet: Through your partnership, the great work of organizations like @KomenAdvocacy, tireless efforts of our private and community partners, research institutions, and public servants, we will endure. We will beat COVID-19. COVID-19 is a virus not a sentence. #KomenonCOVID

name: Dianne Primavera
tweet: Just like doctors supporting cancer patients, we have the best minds in the world responding, developing vaccines, providing care, and more, which gives me hope. #KomenonCOVID

name: Dianne Primavera
tweet: I know this is a daunting time. As cancer survivors and advocates, we know what it means to fight and what it means to care for those around you. #KomenonCOVID

name: Dianne Primavera
tweet: Thank you @KomenAdvocacy for your work to support cancer patients. Coloradans can visit  https://t.co/rugouejnd5 and follow @GovofCO and me on social media for the most recent info and data about the virus. #KomenonCOVID

name: Dianne Primavera
tweet: A6 We’ve also allowed pharmacies to deliver medications to Coloradans in their homes and have given people the opportunity to get a longer supply of their critical medications. #KomenonCOVID

name: Dianne Primavera
tweet: A6 This includes changing policy and reimbursement and encouraging innovative approaches. As a result we are seeing Coloradans use telemedicine and health providers offer this as a service instead of in-person care. #KomenonCOVID

name: Dianne Primavera
tweet: A6 Colorado has really focused on expanding telehealth to ensure that Coloradans can get the care they need without unnecessary exposure to risk. The state is developing a coordinated approach to health information technology and digital health solutions. #KomenonCOVID

name: Dianne Primavera
tweet: A4 We continue working with the federal government to secure critical testing equipment and supplies. #KomenonCOVID

name: Dianne Primavera
tweet: A4 @GovofCO has been a strong advocate for Colorado on the national level and we appreciate the work of our federal delegation who have worked to secure funding for Colorado from the CARES Act. #KomenonCOVID

name: Dianne Primavera
tweet: A3 We have also worked to increase accessibility and affordability of prescription drugs. #KomenonCOVID

name: Dianne Primavera
tweet: A3 The Governor has worked to increase testing, access to paid leave and unemployment insurance, requested emergency federal funding for Colorado small businesses, and has worked to cut through red tape to increase health care accessibility. #KomenonCOVID

name: Dianne Primavera
tweet: A3 Governor Polis has implemented a series of data-based approaches to combat the virus and protect Colorodans, especially our most vulnerable populations. CO is currently under a Stay-at-Home order which has decreased social interactions by 75-80%. #KomenonCOVID

name: Dianne Primavera
tweet: A2 Cancer has taught me to really prioritize my life and not take anything for granted. I’m focused on what I’m grateful for and think that can be a great exercise for Coloradans to do to lift their spirits during this time. #KomenonCOVID #ColoradoStrong

name: Dianne Primavera
tweet: A2 Through our community; our health care professionals, our community leaders, our business partners, our nonprofit organizations, and YOU. #KomenonCOVID

name: Dianne Primavera
tweet: A2 This is a daunting challenge, one that will impact all aspects of our community, ranging from our economy, to our social gatherings, too many of our families, but we will get through this together. #KomenonCOVID

name: Dianne Primavera
tweet: A2 We know this can be scary for many Coloradans, but we are all in this together. All of us must continue to stay at home, wear cloth masks when we leave the house, and continue washing our hands. #KomenonCOVID

name: Dianne Primavera
tweet: A1 It’s easy to feel helpless during this time, but we have to remember the things in our lives we’re grateful for. Similar to cancer, it is reminding us all to prioritize what is really important. #KomenonCOVID

name: Dianne Primavera
tweet: A1 As cancer survivors, we’ve all faced the Grim Reaper before. While cancer was inside our bodies, this is a new kind of battle. COVID-19 is an external and silent threat. #KomenonCOVID

name: Dianne Primavera
tweet: A1 It’s been a lot of conference calls and virtual meetings, but I’m proud of the work our teams are doing during this difficult time. The State of Colorado workforce is almost completely working remotely except for those who cannot complete their work from home. #KomenonCOVID

name: Dianne Primavera
tweet: A1 I’ve been working from home the last 39 days and following physical distancing requirements to ensure I’m protecting myself and my family from potential exposure. As a cancer survivor, I’m considered high risk and I know many other Coloradans are as well. #KomenonCOVID

name: Dianne Primavera
tweet: On #WorldCancerDay, we reflect on those impacted by cancer and the hardships they have faced, as well as celebrating those who have overcome cancer or continuing to fight today. You got this!

name: Dianne Primavera
tweet: As many of you may know, I was diagnosed with cancer four separate times. After nuking my body in treatment, having the fortune of a successful clinical trial, and luck on my side, I fought and I kicked cancer’s butt. #WorldCancerDay  https://t.co/gDhyXGBgjy
